					<div class="sub-li" id="tab1" style="padding:0;">
						<div style="max-height:278px;overflow:auto;margin:2px 5px 5px 10px;padding-bottom:5px;">
							<p><span style="font-size: small;">Men&rsquo;s formal pants haven&rsquo;t changed too much in the last 100 years. The main difference is the height. Men&rsquo;s Victorian pants are usually higher waisted depending on the fashion of the year. Legs were fitted narrowly and tapered to the ankle. Out-seams featured ribbon braids, inspired by military uniforms, for most of the Victorian era. While a single ribbon stripe came about in the late Victorian era.<br />
<br />
Proper trousers are an important part of your men's formal wear ensemble.&nbsp; Our black formal trousers have a single satin stripe down the leg for that added sophisticated style.&nbsp; Since formal trousers are not made with belt loops, these black trousers have an adjustable waist and can be taken in or let out as needed. <br />
<br />
Complete your professional costume look with the ultimate in tuxedo pants. Double pleated for a slim, neat look. Straight waist and satin side stripe give that added sophisticated style. Two sides slit pockets, two brackets with one with button closure to hold your items. Un-hemmed bottom to customize your length. 100% polyester.</span></p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>						</div>
